            I congratulate my hon. Friend on having secured this excellent debate. Is he aware of a recent court ruling to the effect that a worker with long-term sickness who, because an unscrupulous employer will not pay him off, is still on the payroll but not receiving pay, is entitled to statutory holiday of&#x2014;I believe&#x2014;20 days a year? That has to be paid, even though he is not receiving a wage.
